Titolo: Hans Kloss (video game)

Anno: 1992

Descrizione: Hans Kloss is a puzzle-platform game designed by Dariusz Żołna and published in Poland by LK Avalon. It was published in 1992 for the Atari 8-bit family. A Commodore 64 conversion, programmed by Janusz Dąbrowski, was released in 1993. The player controls Hans Kloss, the fictional protagonist of the Polish TV series Stawka większa niż życie, during World War II. He must find plans for a secret weapon in Adolf Hitler's headquarters, the Wolf's Lair.Hans Kloss met with success upon its release, in part thanks to its usage of a popular character. It was praised by reviewers for the quality of its gameplay, graphics and music.

Genere: Puzzle-platform 

Valutazione: N/A
